    <!-- Tips article content -->
    <string name="tip_floating_ball_content">The floating ball shows task status and allows wake-up from outside the app.\nDuring a task, it supports features like supplementary tasks. When idle, it enters companion mode and can be woken anytime. To reduce visual clutter, the floating ball auto-shrinks after a period of inactivity.\nFloating ball and companion mode can be adjusted under Service.</string>
    <string name="tip_accessibility_first_time">First-time setup</string>
    <string name="tip_accessibility_normal_use">Daily use</string>
    <string name="tip_accessibility_revoke_title">Remove accessibility restriction</string>
    <string name="tip_accessibility_revoke_intro">Due to system limits, some OPPO devices require manually removing accessibility restrictions first. (Other brands may not need this. Contact support if you run into issues.)</string>
    <string name="tip_accessibility_revoke_step1">1. Open Accessibility settings and tap TopoClaw;</string>
    <string name="tip_accessibility_revoke_step2">2. Tap the Remove restriction button shown in the figure below;</string>
    <string name="tip_accessibility_revoke_step3">3. Go to Home → long-press TopoClaw icon → App info → Permissions → three-dot menu → Remove all permissions;</string>
    <string name="tip_accessibility_revoke_step4">4. Return to the accessibility page. TopoClaw should no longer be grayed out. Enable it. If you don\'t need physical wake, leave the accessibility shortcut disabled. For setup, see Tips → Physical Wake.</string>
    <string name="tip_screen_share_title">Screen sharing protection</string>
    <string name="tip_screen_share_content">Some devices have screen sharing protection enabled by default, which may cause screenshot failures. Search for it in settings and turn it off.</string>
    <string name="tip_grant_overlay_title">Grant overlay permission</string>
    <string name="tip_grant_overlay_content">First-time use requires overlay permission. Go to Me → Grant overlay permission → find TopoClaw and enable it.</string>
    <string name="tip_normal_use_content">In daily use, start queries in the TopoClaw chat. Grant permissions when prompted. If screenshots fail (check system messages above the chat), re-enable screenshot permission under Me.\n\nThe app relies on vision and accessibility for simulated taps and needs some system permissions. Grant them when requested. For better compatibility with apps that don\'t support accessibility input, we recommend switching to the app\'s built-in keyboard.</string>
    <string name="tip_contact_us_content">For any questions, please contact:\n\nOPPO Research Institute – Data Intelligence Lab – Topology Lab</string>
</resources>
